# Phase 21 — Cloudflare Post-Release Verification

## Objective

Add post-change evidence templates and manual verification gates that must be executed after any Cloudflare production change. This establishes the post-release side of the governance lifecycle, complementing Phase 20 (production readiness review) and Phase 16 (evidence archive).

This phase must NOT deploy, apply, destroy, or mutate Cloudflare. It is a documentation and template layer only.

---

## Branch Name

```
fix/cloudflare-post-release-verification
```

## Commit Message

```
docs(cloudflare): add post-release verification gates
```

---

## Scope

- Create post-release verification overview doc
- Create post-change evidence template (aligned with Phase 16 archive format)
- Create manual verification gates doc
- Create release follow-up checklist
- Update `infra/cloudflare/README.md` with Phase 21 entry

---

## Non-Goals

- Do NOT run `wrangler deploy`, `terraform apply`, `tofu apply`, or any Cloudflare write
- Do NOT print, log, or commit secrets, credentials, or tokens
- Execution of live verification checks is MANUAL — this phase only documents the gates
- Do NOT start or restart any services
- Do NOT edit `/etc/cloudflared/config.yml`
- Do NOT modify files outside Phase 21 scope

---

## Safety Rules

1. All verification steps must be labeled `[MANUAL]` or `[READ-ONLY CHECK]`
2. No automated Cloudflare read or write in templates
3. All examples must use sanitized placeholder values
4. Evidence template must be aligned with Phase 16 archive structure
5. Never print credentials or tokens in any example
6. All docs must clearly separate: verification gate | method | expected result | evidence captured | owner

