## Verification Gates (Cover All in Docs)

After any production Cloudflare change, the following gates must be verified manually:

1. **DNS resolution verified** — All changed DNS records resolve to expected targets
2. **Tunnel route verified** — Tunnel ingress routes traffic correctly to all expected services
3. **Worker route verified** — All modified Worker routes respond correctly (no 4xx/5xx for basic health)
4. **Access policy verified** — Access policies allow expected users and block unexpected access
5. **No unintended route overlap** — No new Worker route overlaps with existing prod routes
6. **No new secret exposure** — No credentials or tokens visible in Worker output, headers, or logs
7. **Rollback still available** — Rollback plan from Phase 12/13 is still executable if needed
8. **Evidence archived** — All required evidence for this change is filed in Phase 16 archive
9. **Owner sign-off complete** — All required owners have reviewed and signed off post-change

---

## Required Deliverables

### Documentation Files

1. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-post-release-verification.md`**
   - Overview of post-release verification process
   - When post-release verification is required (all prod changes)
   - How it links to Phase 16 (evidence archive) and Phase 20 (readiness review)
   - Who conducts the verification
   - What constitutes a verification failure
   - What to do if a gate fails (escalation to Phase 19 DR)

2. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-post-change-evidence-template.md`**
   - Template for filing evidence after a prod change
   - Structure aligned with Phase 16 archive (`docs/infra/evidence/cloudflare/CHANGE-ID/post-release-verification.md`)
   - Required fields:
     - Change ID
     - Change description
     - Date/time of change (UTC)
     - Date/time of verification (UTC)
     - Verifier name/role
     - Per-gate status: `[ ] PASS / FAIL / SKIP`
     - DNS resolution result (read-only, no live query required to file template)
     - Tunnel route result
     - Worker route result
     - Access policy result
     - Route overlap check result
     - Secret exposure check result
     - Rollback availability status
     - Evidence archive link
     - Owner sign-off
   - Sanitized example with placeholder values

3. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-manual-verification-gates.md`**
   - Detailed description of each of the 9 verification gates
   - For each gate: gate name | check method | expected result | pass criteria | fail criteria | evidence to capture
   - All check methods labeled `[MANUAL]` or `[READ-ONLY]`
   - Tool suggestions for each gate (e.g., `dig`, `curl --head`, `wrangler tail --format json`)
   - Important: tool execution is opt-in and MANUAL — not automated by this phase

4. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-release-followup-checklist.md`**
   - Ordered checklist to run after every prod release
   - Sections: Immediate (within 1 hour) | Short-term (within 24 hours) | Closure (within 72 hours)
   - Items:
     - Verify all 9 gates (mark PASS/FAIL/SKIP)
     - Capture any unexpected behavior
     - File post-change evidence in archive
     - Notify owner if any gate FAIL
     - Escalate to DR if critical failure
     - Schedule follow-up if CONDITIONAL
     - Close change record in evidence archive
     - Owner sign-off on closure

5. **`infra/cloudflare/README.md`** *(update)*
   - Add Phase 21 entry with links to all deliverables above

